subject: resource/Go_West_(1940_film)
object: Go West (a.k.a. The Marx Brothers Go West) is the 10th Marx Brothers comedy film, in which brothers Groucho, Chico, and Harpo head to the American West and attempt to unite a couple by ensuring that an evil railroad baron is thwarted.  It was directed by Edward Buzzell and written by Irving Brecher, who receives the original screenplay credit.
